========,1,preface.
Burton is a village in Keya Paha County, Nebraska, United States.
The population was 10 at the 2010 census.
========,2,History.
Burton was platted in 1905.
It was named for a storekeeper.
========,2,Geography.
Burton is located at (42.911358, -99.590992).
According to the United States Census Bureau, the village has a total area of , all of it land.
